HEADWORD: chromesthesia
<hw>chromesthesia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a form of synesthesia in which
nonvisual stimulation results in the experience of color
sensations.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>chromaesthesia</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

